        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 26 at 2:47PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 246 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 7 miles southeast of Montana City to 12 miles
south of Boulder. Movement was east northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Townsend, Boulder, Toston, Wickes, Alhambra, Corbin, Elkhorn State
Park, Winston, Radersburg, Silos, Clancy, Jefferson City, and Goose
Bay.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
